modules.description: This module implements a set of binary serialization and deserialization functions for string sets, supporting operations like size calculation, writing to and reading from binary formats. It provides comparison, S-expression conversion, and pretty-printing capabilities for string sets. Concrete use cases include persisting string sets to disk, transmitting them over a network, or converting them to human-readable representations for debugging.

This module tracks and analyzes character sequences observed during program emulation, providing structured access to detected characters, static strings, and derived word sets. It supports operations to create and inspect prey instances, observe detection and capture events, and serialize string sets. Concrete use cases include analyzing emulated execution traces to extract and persist character sequences, and generating word sets from observed characters for further analysis.
